<quiz>
<question type="description">
        <name>
            <text>7.4.1.3 The inverse of a square matrix</text>
        </name>
        <questiontext format="html">
            <text><![CDATA[
<ul>
    <li>
        <p>
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                A matrix that has no inverse is said to be a
                <b>
                    singular matrix
                </b>
                . A matrix which has an inverse is said to be
                <b>
                    non-singular
                </b>
                .
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                En matrise som ikke har en invers kalles en
                <b>
                    singul&#230;r matrise
                </b>
                . En matrise som har en invers kalles
                <b>
                    ikke-singul&#230;r
                </b>
                .
            </span>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                If a matrix has an inverse then that inverse is unique.
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                Hvis en matrise har en invers, s&#229; er denne inversen unik.
            </span>
        </p>
        <p>
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                Suppose \(B\) and \(C\) are both inverses of \(A\). Then, by definition of the inverse,
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                Anta at \(B\) og \(C\) begge er inverser av \(A\). Da, if&#248;lge definisjonen av inversen, er
            </span>
        </p>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                \(AB = BA = I\) &#226;&#8364;&#402;
                <b>
                    and
                </b>
                &#226;&#8364;&#402; \(AC = CA = I\).
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                \(AB = BA = I\)
                <b>
                    og
                </b>
                \(AC = CA = I\).
            </span>
        </p>
        <p>
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                Consider the two ways of forming the product \(CAB\).
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                Vurder de to m&#229;tene &#229; danne produktet \(CAB\).
            </span>
        </p>
        <ol type="1">
            <li>
                \(CAB = C(AB) = CI = C\).
            </li>
            <li>
                \(CAB = (CA)B = IB = B\).
            </li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                Hence, \(B = C\) and the
                <b>
                    inverse is unique
                </b>
                .
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                Alts&#229;, \(B = C\) og den
                <b>
                    inversen er unik
                </b>
                .
            </span>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                There is no such operation as division in matrix algebra.
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                Det finnes ingen operasjon som heter divisjon i matrisearitmetikk.
            </span>
        </p>
        <p>
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                We do not write \(\dfrac{B}{A}\) but rather \(A^{-1}B\) or \(BA^{-1}\), depending on the order required.
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                Vi skriver ikke \(\dfrac{B}{A}\) men heller \(A^{-1}B\) eller \(BA^{-1}\), avhengig av rekkef&#248;lgen som kreves.
            </span>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                Assuming that the square matrix \(A\) has an inverse \(A^{-1}\) then the solution of the systems of equations \(AX = B\) is found by pre-multiplying both sides by \(A^{-1}\).
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                Forutsatt at den kvadratiske matrisen \(A\) har en invers \(A^{-1}\), s&#229; finnes l&#248;sningen p&#229; systemet med ligninger \(AX = B\) ved &#229; multiplisere begge sider p&#229; forh&#229;nd med \(A^{-1}\).
            </span>
        </p>
        <div>
            <center>
            </center>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
            \(AX\)\(=\)\(B\)
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                pre-multiplying by \(A^{-1}\): &#226;&#8364;&#402;
                                                                \(A^{-1}(AX)\)
                                                                \(=\)
                                                                \(A^{-1}B\),
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                multipliserer p&#229; forh&#229;nd \(A^{-1}\):
                                                                \(A^{-1}(AX)\)
                                                                \(=\)
                                                                \(A^{-1}B\),
            </span>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                using associativity:
                                                                \((A^{-1}A)X\)
                                                                \(=\)
                                                                \(B\),
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                ved bruk av assosiativitet:
                                                                \((A^{-1}A)X\)
                                                                \(=\)
                                                                \(B\),
            </span>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                using \(A^{-1}A = \):
                                                                \(IX\)
                                                                \(=\)
                                                                \(A^{-1}B\),
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                ved bruk av \(A^{-1}A = \):
                                                                \(IX\)
                                                                \(=\)
                                                                \(A^{-1}B\),
            </span>
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p style="text-align: center;">
            <span class="multilang" lang="en">
                using property of \(I\):
                                                                \(X\)
                                                                \(=\)
                                                                \(A^{-1}B\)
                                                                &#226;&#8364;&#402; which is the solution we seek.
            </span>
            <span class="multilang" lang="no">
                ved bruk av egenskapen \(I\):
                                                                \(X\)
                                                                \(=\)
                                                                \(A^{-1}B\)
                                                                , som er l&#248;sningen vi ser etter.
            </span>
        </p>
    </li>
</ul>
]]></text>
